{"TopicId":173237,"ForumId":97,"TopicTitle":"Mk 2 pod doesn\u0026#039;t float right","CreatedByName":"Capt. Hunt","CreatedById":97860,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T03:46:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Capt. Hunt","CreatedById":97860,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T03:46:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know this is kinda silly, but the pod modeled after the Gemini capsule likes to float nose up like the other pods.\u00A0 is there an easy way to tweak the buoyancy to get it to float on its side?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbinchaser","CreatedById":160817,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T04:23:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure, but I actually think it\u0027s modeled after the Mercury pod, otherwise it would have a 2 crew capacity.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-30T04:23:43Z\u0022 title=\u002203/30/2018 04:23  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 30, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Lo Var Lachland\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Delbrutis","CreatedById":144613,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T04:53:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this would require changing the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E of the capsule. And I\u0027m not sure there is a way to do it to a degree that it would float like you want and fly acceptable? Now that I\u0027m seeing some new air bag parts show up. I was thinking of rummaging through my old drive and see if I could find those cool old Klockheed Marten Airbag parts that stopped working and see if I could figure out how to get the buoyancy going again?\u00A0 They had a pair of side saddle Gemini style bags. If you had something like that you could just drop the buoyancy on the pod way\u00A0 down and let the bags take the load. Problem is most of the new air bag mods I have seen \u0022I think\u0022 are mostly aesthetic. I don\u0027t think any of them change the buoyancy when they inflate like the old Klockheed marten bags did.\u00A0 Sorry maybe someone else knows better than me but I think the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E determines how your capsule floats.\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223339322\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173237\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522383805\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160817\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lo Var Lachland\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, Lo Var Lachland said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure, but I actually think it\u0027s modeled after the Mercury pod, otherwise it would have a 2 crew capacity.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think he is talking about the new MK2 in the DLC ? It does have 2 crew and is modelled after the Gemini.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-30T04:58:43Z\u0022 title=\u002203/30/2018 04:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 30, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Delbrutis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbinchaser","CreatedById":160817,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T05:03:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223339350\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173237\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522385608\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144613\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Delbrutis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Delbrutis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think he is talking about the new MK2 in the DLC ? It does have 2 crew and is modelled after the Gemini.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAHA, he never mentioned that. Thanks.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T06:17:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMercury is the Mk1 pod.\u00A0 Gemini is Mk2, Apollo is Mk1-3..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-30T06:17:28Z\u0022 title=\u002203/30/2018 06:17  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 30, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by klesh\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Capt. Hunt","CreatedById":97860,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T06:29:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223339362\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173237\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522386190\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160817\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lo Var Lachland\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Lo Var Lachland said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAHA, he never mentioned that. Thanks.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, considering this is the Making History Discussion board, and the Mk 2 is specified in the title, and that I specifically mentioned Gemini, isn\u0027t it kinda implied that I\u0027m talking about the Mk 2? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m looking at \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/168058-icecovery/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022168058\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/168058-icecovery/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Icecovery\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s Comfortable Landing mod, it does appear to have code that changes the buoyancy and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E when inflated.\u00A0 I\u0027ll take a look at that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: ok, judging by his code for the BDB and FASA gemini capsules, his config for the mk 2 isn\u0027t set up to actually change anything, so I\u0027ll have to play around with it, but it looks like it\u0027ll work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-30T06:46:34Z\u0022 title=\u002203/30/2018 06:46  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 30, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Capt. Hunt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbinchaser","CreatedById":160817,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T07:56:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223339420\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173237\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522391382\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297860\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Capt. Hunt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Capt. Hunt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, considering this is the Making History Discussion board, and the Mk 2 is specified in the title, and that I specifically mentioned Gemini, isn\u0027t it kinda implied that I\u0027m talking about the Mk 2? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright, alright, sheesh. I didn\u0027t notice the sub-forum.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Icecovery","CreatedById":168058,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T16:33:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223339420\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173237\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522391382\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297860\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Capt. Hunt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Capt. Hunt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, considering this is the Making History Discussion board, and the Mk 2 is specified in the title, and that I specifically mentioned Gemini, isn\u0027t it kinda implied that I\u0027m talking about the Mk 2? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\