ata-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173237\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522390638\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klesh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, klesh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMercury is the Mk1 pod.\u00A0 Gemini is Mk2, Apollo is Mk1-3..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMk2 \u003Cu\u003Epod\u003C/u\u003E is the Gemini capsule.\u00A0 Mk2 \u003Cu\u003Ecockpit\u003C/u\u003E and \u003Cu\u003Einline\u003C/u\u003E are the Mk2-profile spaceplane parts.\u00A0 Size 1 is 1.25m, Size 1.5 is 1.875m, size 2 is 2.5m, size 3 is 3.75m, presumably\u00A05m is size 4?\u00A0 Mk3 is pretty clear, and Mk1 is (I guess) 1.25m spaceplane/airplane parts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese are not logical conventions... but it\u0027s what we have?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T16:53:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow you\u0027re just being pedantic.\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Capt. Hunt","CreatedById":97860,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-31T05:34:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223339898\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173237\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522427626\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168058\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Icecovery\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Icecovery said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes,\u00A0I didn\u0027t actually set it up, for some reason, it didn\u0027t work very well. If you make it work\u00A0please let me know, so I can add it to the next version of the update.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nok, I used the same offsets as your config for the BDB and FASA Gemini capsules, it still wants to float upright and when I tip it over it still likes to float very high in the water.\u00A0 If I\u0027m lucky the swells kiss the bottom of the flotation bag.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-31T05:35:53Z\u0022 title=\u002203/31/2018 05:35  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 31, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Capt. Hunt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}